{"key":"processedPost-14387099","value":{"id":14387099,"first":14386035,"last":14389048,"when":1304340892,"utime":"05/02/11 03:54 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>zzantium2999 said:</b><br />Put a humidifier or 2 on the top shelf so the humidity falls. Put the heater on the bottom shelf so the heat rises.<br /></blockquote><br /><br />Two things here.&nbsp; First of all, humidity rises, not falls.&nbsp; The humidifier should be on the bottom shelf.&nbsp; Second, you don't heat indoor greenhouses for the reason condensation will form on the walls, which 'steals' your humidity in order create that condensation.<br /><br />If necessary, heat the room your greenhouse is in, but not the greenhouse itself.<br />RR","title":"Re: heaters that can be in %60-%100 humidity?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}